Corporate Pensions to Sell $32.5 Billion in Liabilities, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-05-23T01:20:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/corporate-pensions-to-sell-32-5-billion-in-liabilities-ft-says.html
U.K. corporate pension plans will
sell about 20 billion pounds ($32.5 billion) worth of defined-
benefit liabilities to banks and insurers over the next year and
a half, the Financial Times reported, citing James Mullins, a
partner at Hymans Robertson Ltd.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 